-- Orpea Says It's `Particularly Confident' of Reaching 2010 Revenue Target
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-11-09T05:07:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/orpea-says-it-s-particularly-confident-of-reaching-2010-revenue-target.html
Orpea SA, France’s largest commercial
retirement-home operator, said it’s particularly confident of
reaching its 2010 revenue target after third-quarter sales
gained 13 percent.  Revenue in the first nine months increased 15 percent to
714.2 million euros, the company said in a statement in Les
Echos newspaper, without giving the third-quarter total.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  